.TH "amdgpu_vm_handle_fault" 9 "amdgpu_vm_handle_fault" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdgpu_vm_handle_fault \- graceful handling of VM faults.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" amdgpu_vm_handle_fault
.BI "(struct amdgpu_device *adev "  ","
.BI "u32 pasid "  ","
.BI "uint64_t addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adev" 12
amdgpu device pointer
.IP "pasid" 12
PASID of the VM
.IP "addr" 12
Address of the fault
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Try to gracefully handle a VM fault. Return true if the fault was handled and
shouldn't be reported any more.
